<p>Footloose: She teamed the look with ripped denim jeans, while the boot casts went up to below the knee</p>

<p>The couple couldn't keep their hands off each other as they sat down for an alfresco lunch and were pictured passionately kissing.</p>

<p>Their outing comes as Katie took to Instagram stories after being mocked by fans for mispronouncing Carl's name. </p>

<p>Poking fun at herself, the mother-of-five said: So many people keep on saying that I call Carl C-A-R-L "Cole," when I know I should be saying Carl. </p>

<p>Nasty injury: Katie has been left unable to walk on her feet and Carl often carries her as opposed to using a wheel chair</p>

<p>Ouch: The star broke both of her feet after jumping off a wall at a theme back in Turkey, and needed major surgery last month to fuse the bones back together</p>

<p>'I just can't say Carl, Carl come upstairs, Carl. I just say Cole. I'm trying to tell Cole to watch my story. Carl, can you watch my story?'</p>

<p>The camera then panned over to the former Love Island question who swore.  </p>

<p>The television personality reportedly calls herself 'Katie Woods' after just three months of dating Carl.</p>

<p>According to a source, the glamour model has already splashed out on a K WOODS number plate for her scooter and new car. </p>

<p>Smitten: The couple kissed each other as they waited for lunch </p>

<p>Laidback look: Carl, meanwhile, was casually-clad in a black T-shirt, jeans and trainers</p>

<p>Her knight in shining armour: At one point Katie sat on Carl's knee </p>

<p>An insider told The Sun: 'Katie's head over heels for him and calls herself 'Katie Woods' all the time.</p>

<p>'She's even getting a number plate calling her K WOODS to go on new car and scooter next week.</p>

<p>'Nobody would be surprised if they were married by the end of the year.'</p>

<p>MailOnline has contacted Katie Price's representatives for comment.  </p>

<p>The glamour model has been dating former Love Island star Carl for three months, yet things have moved very quickly between the pair.  </p>

